Fix bootgen -verify segfault (NULL pointer dereference on iHT)

VerifyAuthentication() calls ReadBinaryFile() which only dispatches to
ReadPartitions(). Since ReadHeaderTableDetails() was never called, the
image header table pointer (iHT) is NULL, causing a segfault when
VerifyAuthentication() tries to access iHT->headerAuthCertificateWordOffset.

Fix by calling ReadHeaderTableDetails() before ReadBinaryFile() in
VerifyAuthentication(), which initializes the boot header, image header
table, partition headers, and auth certificates needed for verification.

https://github.com/Xilinx/bootgen/issues/30

--- a/zynqmp/src/verifyimage-zynqmp.cpp
+++ b/zynqmp/src/verifyimage-zynqmp.cpp
@@ -50,6 +50,7 @@
 /*******************************************************************************/
 void ZynqMpReadImage::VerifyAuthentication(bool verifyImageOption)
 {
+    ReadHeaderTableDetails();
     ReadBinaryFile();

     if (iHT->headerAuthCertificateWordOffset != 0)
